headline.main: HAVANA.; Cuban Affairs--Another Slaver--Business, &c. To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times:

docs.lead_paragraph: I have no disposition ever to weary your readers with immaterial things, and if they appear trivial at times, it is because I fail in giving the explanation that associates them with the vitality of social organization here, or defines their intended influence upon the friendship and commercial intercourse of the "two races," a fault caused by imputing knowledge which can only be had by contact and residence in this community.

docs.lead_paragraph: To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times: Your papers of 9th of February and 7th of March last, containing a biographical notice of the late Doctor THOMAS COOPER, have just fallen under the eye of Mrs. COOPER, the widow of the subject of the Memoir. She resides with her youngest daughter, my wife, and is, though aged, in the enjoyment of good health and the possession of all the faculties of her mind.

headline.main: The Romance of Crline--The Suspected Murderer Parks.

docs.lead_paragraph: From the Buffalo Commercial Advertiser. Our readers have doubtless read the paragraphs which have been circulating in the papers respecting the man PARKS, the supposed murderer of the Englishman BEATSON, at Cuyahoa Falls, and his imagined identity with a noted English burglar named DICKINSON, who fled from justice in his native land, and arrived in this country some years since.

headline.main: WEST COAST OF AFRICA.; The Slave Trade--Palm Oil Trade.
FRANCE.; Mischance to the Empress--Montalembert's Motion Missed Fire--Napoleon the First's Legates--More Arrests--Illness of De Tocqueville and Lammenals, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Moniteur announces non-officially that the Empress "qui etail enceinte depuis deux mois, et qui etail souffrante depuis quelques jours, a fait une fausse couche dans la soiree du 29 April." Her Majesty's state of health is again satisfactory.

docs.lead_paragraph: The health of the Isthmus was never better says the Panama Herald, than at present. On the 25th, a destructive fire broke out at Gorgona, consuming the entire village, with the exception of the office of Messrs. RAN RUNNELS and HINCKLEY.
